Spot the difference:

\newcommand\wvlinevar[1]{{\global\savedwidth\arrayrulewidth%
\global\arrayrulewidth #1}%
\vline {\global\arrayrulewidth\savedwidth}\ignorespaces}

The point is this: something like \wvlineconst automatically eats up any
following spaces (that's a TeX rule) whereas something like \wvlinevar{1pt}
will not and the following space gets counted.  So, the command
\ignorespaces is necessary to avoid the extra space, which is what is
causing the positional shift.

